 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "source": [
    "## Himmelblau sampling example"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The Himmelblau function is a classical test function for optimization. It is not necessarily hard to appraise, but it gives us a good reference point when investigating priors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import hmc_tomography"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we create the Himmelblau target. It is always 2 dimensional, so we don't have to pass that along. Additionally, we create an 'unbounded uniform' distribution, which is zero everywhere on the real line. It is not necessarily *no information*, as it already gives preference to specific orders of magnitude. Lastly, we'll create a unit mass matrix, by lack of a better idea."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "target = hmc_tomography.Targets.Himmelblau(annealing=50)\n",
    "prior = hmc_tomography.Priors.Uniform(target.dimensions)\n",
    "mass_matrix = hmc_tomography.MassMatrices.Unit(target.dimensions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Assemble all of it in a sampler object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sampler = hmc_tomography.Samplers.HMC(target, mass_matrix, prior)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Start sampling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** \n",
    "\n",
    "Note that I explicitly overwrite the previously generated samples. Sometimes when re-running a code lots of times, it might get tedious to go through the user-interaction for defining new filenames. Use this function at your own risk!\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "sys:1: Warning: \n",
      "Silently overwriting existing samples file (samples_himmelblau.h5) if it exists.\n",
      "Tot. acc rate: 0.77. Last 100 acc rate: 0.79. Progress: 100%|██████████| 50000/50000 [00:17<00:00, 2787.43it/s]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sampler.sample(\"samples_himmelblau.h5\", \n",
    "               overwrite_samples=True, \n",
    "               proposals=50000, \n",
    "               online_thinning=10, \n",
    "               time_step=0.75, \n",
    "               sample_ram_buffer_size=137);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And visualize the samples:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** \n",
    "\n",
    "Using the sampler.samples_filename allows us to use an updated filename. If you don't use the `overwite_samples` variable when sampling, you might be prompted for a new filename if the samples file already exists. This chosen filename is stored in `HMC.samples_filename`, for later use, such as loading samples.\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1008x576 with 5 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with hmc_tomography.Post.Samples(sampler.samples_filename) as samples:\n",
    "    hmc_tomography.Post.Visualization.visualize_2_dimensions(samples, bins=30, show=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,

   "source": []
  }
